                    <comment id="13137194" author="rcmuir" created="Thu, 27 Oct 2011 16:04:28 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for opening this issue James.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I updated the patch: for just a one-off comparator (merging distributed results), termsenum/fuzzytermsenum/automata construction is very costly, so I just implemented this the standard way (as LuceneLevenshteinDistance).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Just like before, DirectSpellChecker doesn&apos;t actually use this code, but the distances computations are equivalent.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                    <comment id="13137201" author="rcmuir" created="Thu, 27 Oct 2011 16:15:43 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;fix dyslexic patch name, and add another test term that will fail if the distance measure doesn&apos;t act like lucene&apos;s&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
